article.headline: Dayton 55, Coppin St 42
article.story: DAYTON, Ohio (AP) -- Marques Bennett made all four of his 3-point attempts and grabbed eight rebounds to lead Dayton to a 55-42 win over Coppin State on Saturday. Monty Scott hit 3 of 5 from long range to add 11 points for Dayton (1-1), which shot 43 percent from 3-point range. Dayton built a 30-19 halftime lead, but Coppin State (0-2) outscored the Flyers 15-7 over the first nine minutes of the second half to get to within 37-34. Dayton countered with 4-of-7 3-point shooting -- including two by Bennett -- to pull away. Nicholas King scored 13 for Coppin State, and Raheem Scott added 11 points. Dayton's Trent Meacham had five assists, and the Flyers bench outscored Coppin State's reserves 36-9.
